Options.Documentation: Specify true to return only the most critical recommendations. The default is false, which returns all recommendations.

Options.Documentation: Return only channels specified in the filter. Filter is specified by using OData syntax. Example: $filter=channels eq 'Api' or channel eq 'Notification'

Options.Documentation: Name of SKU used to filter the regions.

Options.Name: linux_workers_enabled
Options.Documentation: Specify true if you want to filter to only regions that support Linux workers.

Options.Documentation: A JSON representation of the app properties. See example.

Options.Name: kind
Options.Documentation: Kind of resource.

Options.Name: location
Options.Documentation: Resource Location.

Options.Name: enabled
Options.Documentation: true if the app is enabled; otherwise, false. Setting this value to false disables the app (takes the app offline).

Options.Name: host_name_ssl_states
Options.Documentation: Hostname SSL states are used to manage the SSL bindings for app's hostnames.

SubOptions.Name: virtual_ip
SubOptions.Documentation: Virtual IP address assigned to the hostname if IP based SSL is enabled.

SubOptions.Name: to_update
SubOptions.Documentation: Set to true to update existing hostname.

SubOptions.Name: host_type
SubOptions.Documentation: Indicates whether the hostname is a standard or repository hostname. Possible values include: 'Standard', 'Repository'

Options.Name: server_farm_id
Options.Documentation: Resource ID of the associated App Service plan, formatted as: "/subscriptions/{subscriptionID}/resourceGroups/{groupName}/providers/Microsoft.Web/serverfarms/{appServicePlanName}".

Options.Name: reserved
Options.Documentation: true if reserved; otherwise, false.

Options.Name: site_config
Options.Documentation: Configuration of the app.

SubOptions.Name: request_tracing_enabled
SubOptions.Documentation: true if request tracing is enabled; otherwise, false.

SubOptions.Name: remote_debugging_enabled
SubOptions.Documentation: true if remote debugging is enabled; otherwise, false.

SubOptions.Name: http_logging_enabled
SubOptions.Documentation: true if HTTP logging is enabled; otherwise, false.

SubOptions.Name: detailed_error_logging_enabled
SubOptions.Documentation: true if detailed error logging is enabled; otherwise, false.

SubOptions.Name: type
SubOptions.Documentation: Type of database. Possible values include: 'MySql', 'SQLServer', 'SQLAzure', 'Custom', 'NotificationHub', 'ServiceBus', 'EventHub', 'ApiHub', 'DocDb', 'RedisCache', 'PostgreSQL'

SubOptions.Name: extension
SubOptions.Documentation: Requests with this extension will be handled using the specified FastCGI application.

SubOptions.Name: script_processor
SubOptions.Documentation: The absolute path to the FastCGI application.

SubOptions.Name: arguments
SubOptions.Documentation: Command-line arguments to be passed to the script processor.

SubOptions.Name: always_on
SubOptions.Documentation: true if Always On is enabled; otherwise, false.

SubOptions.Name: managed_pipeline_mode
SubOptions.Documentation: Managed pipeline mode. Possible values include: 'Integrated', 'Classic'

SubOptions.Name: load_balancing
SubOptions.Documentation: Site load balancing. Possible values include: 'WeightedRoundRobin', 'LeastRequests', 'LeastResponseTime', 'WeightedTotalTraffic', 'RequestHash'

SubOptions.Name: experiments
SubOptions.Documentation: This is work around for polymophic types.

SubOptions.Name: action_host_name
SubOptions.Documentation: Hostname of a slot to which the traffic will be redirected if decided to. E.g. myapp-stage.azurewebsites.net.

SubOptions.Name: reroute_percentage
SubOptions.Documentation: Percentage of the traffic which will be redirected to ActionHostName.

SubOptions.Name: change_step
SubOptions.Documentation: In auto ramp up scenario this is the step to to add/remove from ReroutePercentage until it reaches MinReroutePercentage or MaxReroutePercentage. Site metrics are checked every N minutes specificed in ChangeIntervalInMinutes. Custom decision algorithm can be provided in TiPCallback site extension which URL can be specified in ChangeDecisionCallbackUrl.

SubOptions.Name: change_interval_in_minutes
SubOptions.Documentation: Specifies interval in mimuntes to reevaluate ReroutePercentage.

SubOptions.Name: min_reroute_percentage
SubOptions.Documentation: Specifies lower boundary above which ReroutePercentage will stay.

SubOptions.Name: max_reroute_percentage
SubOptions.Documentation: Specifies upper boundary below which ReroutePercentage will stay.

SubOptions.Name: change_decision_callback_url
SubOptions.Documentation:
Custom decision algorithm can be provided in TiPCallback site extension which URL can be specified. See TiPCallback site extension for the scaffold and contracts.
https://www.siteextensions.net/packages/TiPCallback/

SubOptions.Name: name
SubOptions.Documentation: Name of the routing rule. The recommended name would be to point to the slot which will receive the traffic in the experiment.

SubOptions.Name: max_memory_in_mb
SubOptions.Documentation: Maximum allowed memory usage in MB.

SubOptions.Name: max_disk_size_in_mb
SubOptions.Documentation: Maximum allowed disk size usage in MB.

SubOptions.Name: auto_heal_enabled
SubOptions.Documentation: true if Auto Heal is enabled; otherwise, false.

SubOptions.Name: triggers
SubOptions.Documentation: Conditions that describe when to execute the auto-heal actions.

SubOptions.Name: requests
SubOptions.Documentation: A rule based on total requests.

SubOptions.Name: private_bytes_in_kb
SubOptions.Documentation: A rule based on private bytes.

SubOptions.Name: status_codes
SubOptions.Documentation: A rule based on status codes.

SubOptions.Name: slow_requests
SubOptions.Documentation: A rule based on request execution time.

SubOptions.Name: actions
SubOptions.Documentation: Actions to be executed when a rule is triggered.

SubOptions.Name: action_type
SubOptions.Documentation: Predefined action to be taken. Possible values include: 'Recycle', 'LogEvent', 'CustomAction'

SubOptions.Name: min_process_execution_time
SubOptions.Documentation:
Minimum time the process must execute
before taking the action

SubOptions.Name: allowed_origins
SubOptions.Documentation:
Gets or sets the list of origins that should be allowed to make cross-origin
calls (for example: http://example.com:12345). Use "*" to allow all.

SubOptions.Name: is_push_enabled
SubOptions.Documentation: Gets or sets a flag indicating whether the Push endpoint is enabled.

SubOptions.Name: tag_whitelist_json
SubOptions.Documentation: Gets or sets a JSON string containing a list of tags that are whitelisted for use by the push registration endpoint.

SubOptions.Name: tags_requiring_auth
SubOptions.Documentation:
Gets or sets a JSON string containing a list of tags that require user authentication to be used in the push registration endpoint.
Tags can consist of alphanumeric characters and the following:
'_', '@', '#', '.', ':', '-'. 
Validation should be performed at the PushRequestHandler.

SubOptions.Name: dynamic_tags_json
SubOptions.Documentation: Gets or sets a JSON string containing a list of dynamic tags that will be evaluated from user claims in the push registration endpoint.

SubOptions.Name: api_definition
SubOptions.Documentation: Information about the formal API definition for the app.

SubOptions.Name: url
SubOptions.Documentation: The URL of the API definition.

SubOptions.Name: ip_address
SubOptions.Documentation: IP address the security restriction is valid for.

SubOptions.Name: subnet_mask
SubOptions.Documentation: Subnet mask for the range of IP addresses the restriction is valid for.

Options.Name: scm_site_also_stopped
Options.Documentation: true to stop SCM (KUDU) site when the app is stopped; otherwise, false. The default is false.

Options.Name: hosting_environment_profile
Options.Documentation: App Service Environment to use for the app.

SubOptions.Name: id
SubOptions.Documentation: Resource ID of the App Service Environment.

Options.Name: client_affinity_enabled
Options.Documentation: true to enable client affinity; false to stop sending session affinity cookies, which route client requests in the same session to the same instance. Default is true.

Options.Name: client_cert_enabled
Options.Documentation: true to enable client certificate authentication (TLS mutual authentication); otherwise, false. Default is false.

Options.Name: host_names_disabled
Options.Documentation: true to disable the public hostnames of the app; otherwise, false. If true, the app is only accessible via API management process.

Options.Name: container_size
Options.Documentation: Size of the function container.

Options.Name: daily_memory_time_quota
Options.Documentation: Maximum allowed daily memory-time quota (applicable on dynamic apps only).

Options.Name: cloning_info
Options.Documentation: If specified during app creation, the app is cloned from a source app.

SubOptions.Name: correlation_id
SubOptions.Documentation:
Correlation ID of cloning operation. This ID ties multiple cloning operations
together to use the same snapshot.

SubOptions.Name: clone_custom_host_names
SubOptions.Documentation: true to clone custom hostnames from source app; otherwise, false.

SubOptions.Name: clone_source_control
SubOptions.Documentation: true to clone source control from source app; otherwise, false.

SubOptions.Name: source_web_app_id
SubOptions.Documentation:
ARM resource ID of the source app. App resource ID is of the form 
/subscriptions/{subId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Web/sites/{siteName} for production slots and 
/subscriptions/{subId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Web/sites/{siteName}/slots/{slotName} for other slots.

SubOptions.Name: app_settings_overrides
SubOptions.Documentation:
Application setting overrides for cloned app. If specified, these settings override the settings cloned 
from source app. Otherwise, application settings from source app are retained.

SubOptions.Name: configure_load_balancing
SubOptions.Documentation: true to configure load balancing for source and destination app.

SubOptions.Name: traffic_manager_profile_id
SubOptions.Documentation:
ARM resource ID of the Traffic Manager profile to use, if it exists. Traffic Manager resource ID is of the form 
/subscriptions/{subId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Network/trafficManagerProfiles/{profileName}.

SubOptions.Name: traffic_manager_profile_name
SubOptions.Documentation: Name of Traffic Manager profile to create. This is only needed if Traffic Manager profile does not already exist.

SubOptions.Name: ignore_quotas
SubOptions.Documentation: true if quotas should be ignored; otherwise, false.

Options.Name: snapshot_info
Options.Documentation: If specified during app creation, the app is created from a previous snapshot.

SubOptions.Name: snapshot_time
SubOptions.Documentation: Point in time in which the app recovery should be attempted, formatted as a DateTime string.

SubOptions.Name: recovery_target
SubOptions.Documentation: Specifies the web app that snapshot contents will be written to.

SubOptions.Name: location
SubOptions.Documentation: Geographical location of the target web app, e.g. SouthEastAsia, SouthCentralUS

SubOptions.Name: id
SubOptions.Documentation:
ARM resource ID of the target app. 
/subscriptions/{subId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Web/sites/{siteName} for production slots and 
/subscriptions/{subId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Web/sites/{siteName}/slots/{slotName} for other slots.

SubOptions.Name: overwrite
SubOptions.Documentation: If true the recovery operation can overwrite source app; otherwise, false.

SubOptions.Name: recover_configuration
SubOptions.Documentation: If true, site configuration, in addition to content, will be reverted.

SubOptions.Name: ignore_conflicting_host_names
SubOptions.Documentation:
If true, custom hostname conflicts will be ignored when recovering to a target web app.
This setting is only necessary when RecoverConfiguration is enabled.

Options.Name: https_only
Options.Documentation:
HttpsOnly: configures a web site to accept only https requests. Issues redirect for
http requests

Options.Name: skip_dns_registration
Options.Documentation:
If true web app hostname is not registered with DNS on creation. This parameter is
 only used for app creation.

Options.Name: skip_custom_domain_verification
Options.Documentation: If true, custom (non *.azurewebsites.net) domains associated with web app are not verified.

Options.Name: force_dns_registration
Options.Documentation: If true, web app hostname is force registered with DNS.

Options.Name: ttl_in_seconds
Options.Documentation: Time to live in seconds for web app's default domain name.

ResponseFields.Name: usage_state
ResponseFields.Description: State indicating whether the app has exceeded its quota usage. Read-only. Possible values include: 'Normal', 'Exceeded'

ResponseFields.Name: enabled
ResponseFields.Description: true if the app is enabled; otherwise, false. Setting this value to false disables the app (takes the app offline).

ResponseFields.Name: enabled_host_names
ResponseFields.Description:
Enabled hostnames for the app.Hostnames need to be assigned (see HostNames) AND enabled. Otherwise,
the app is not served on those hostnames.

ResponseFields.Name: availability_state
ResponseFields.Description: Management information availability state for the app. Possible values include: 'Normal', 'Limited', 'DisasterRecoveryMode'

ResponseFields.Name: host_name_ssl_states
ResponseFields.Description: Hostname SSL states are used to manage the SSL bindings for app's hostnames.

SubFields.Name: virtual_ip
SubFields.Description: Virtual IP address assigned to the hostname if IP based SSL is enabled.

SubFields.Name: to_update
SubFields.Description: Set to true to update existing hostname.

SubFields.Name: host_type
SubFields.Description: Indicates whether the hostname is a standard or repository hostname. Possible values include: 'Standard', 'Repository'

ResponseFields.Name: server_farm_id
ResponseFields.Description: Resource ID of the associated App Service plan, formatted as: "/subscriptions/{subscriptionID}/resourceGroups/{groupName}/providers/Microsoft.Web/serverfarms/{appServicePlanName}".

ResponseFields.Name: reserved
ResponseFields.Description: true if reserved; otherwise, false.

ResponseFields.Name: last_modified_time_utc
ResponseFields.Description: Last time the app was modified, in UTC. Read-only.

ResponseFields.Name: site_config
ResponseFields.Description: Configuration of the app.

SubFields.Name: request_tracing_enabled
SubFields.Description: true if request tracing is enabled; otherwise, false.

SubFields.Name: remote_debugging_enabled
SubFields.Description: true if remote debugging is enabled; otherwise, false.

SubFields.Name: http_logging_enabled
SubFields.Description: true if HTTP logging is enabled; otherwise, false.

SubFields.Name: detailed_error_logging_enabled
SubFields.Description: true if detailed error logging is enabled; otherwise, false.

SubFields.Name: type
SubFields.Description: Type of database. Possible values include: 'MySql', 'SQLServer', 'SQLAzure', 'Custom', 'NotificationHub', 'ServiceBus', 'EventHub', 'ApiHub', 'DocDb', 'RedisCache', 'PostgreSQL'

SubFields.Name: extension
SubFields.Description: Requests with this extension will be handled using the specified FastCGI application.

SubFields.Name: script_processor
SubFields.Description: The absolute path to the FastCGI application.

SubFields.Name: arguments
SubFields.Description: Command-line arguments to be passed to the script processor.

SubFields.Name: always_on
SubFields.Description: true if Always On is enabled; otherwise, false.

SubFields.Name: managed_pipeline_mode
SubFields.Description: Managed pipeline mode. Possible values include: 'Integrated', 'Classic'

SubFields.Name: load_balancing
SubFields.Description: Site load balancing. Possible values include: 'WeightedRoundRobin', 'LeastRequests', 'LeastResponseTime', 'WeightedTotalTraffic', 'RequestHash'

SubFields.Name: experiments
SubFields.Description: This is work around for polymophic types.

SubFields.Name: action_host_name
SubFields.Description: Hostname of a slot to which the traffic will be redirected if decided to. E.g. myapp-stage.azurewebsites.net.

SubFields.Name: reroute_percentage
SubFields.Description: Percentage of the traffic which will be redirected to ActionHostName.

SubFields.Name: change_step
SubFields.Description: In auto ramp up scenario this is the step to to add/remove from ReroutePercentage until it reaches MinReroutePercentage or MaxReroutePercentage. Site metrics are checked every N minutes specificed in ChangeIntervalInMinutes. Custom decision algorithm can be provided in TiPCallback site extension which URL can be specified in ChangeDecisionCallbackUrl.

SubFields.Name: change_interval_in_minutes
SubFields.Description: Specifies interval in mimuntes to reevaluate ReroutePercentage.

SubFields.Name: min_reroute_percentage
SubFields.Description: Specifies lower boundary above which ReroutePercentage will stay.

SubFields.Name: max_reroute_percentage
SubFields.Description: Specifies upper boundary below which ReroutePercentage will stay.

SubFields.Name: change_decision_callback_url
SubFields.Description:
Custom decision algorithm can be provided in TiPCallback site extension which URL can be specified. See TiPCallback site extension for the scaffold and contracts.
https://www.siteextensions.net/packages/TiPCallback/

SubFields.Name: name
SubFields.Description: Name of the routing rule. The recommended name would be to point to the slot which will receive the traffic in the experiment.

SubFields.Name: max_memory_in_mb
SubFields.Description: Maximum allowed memory usage in MB.

SubFields.Name: max_disk_size_in_mb
SubFields.Description: Maximum allowed disk size usage in MB.

SubFields.Name: auto_heal_enabled
SubFields.Description: true if Auto Heal is enabled; otherwise, false.

SubFields.Name: triggers
SubFields.Description: Conditions that describe when to execute the auto-heal actions.

SubFields.Name: requests
SubFields.Description: A rule based on total requests.

SubFields.Name: private_bytes_in_kb
SubFields.Description: A rule based on private bytes.

SubFields.Name: status_codes
SubFields.Description: A rule based on status codes.

SubFields.Name: slow_requests
SubFields.Description: A rule based on request execution time.

SubFields.Name: actions
SubFields.Description: Actions to be executed when a rule is triggered.

SubFields.Name: action_type
SubFields.Description: Predefined action to be taken. Possible values include: 'Recycle', 'LogEvent', 'CustomAction'

SubFields.Name: min_process_execution_time
SubFields.Description:
Minimum time the process must execute
before taking the action

SubFields.Name: allowed_origins
SubFields.Description:
Gets or sets the list of origins that should be allowed to make cross-origin
calls (for example: http://example.com:12345). Use "*" to allow all.

SubFields.Name: is_push_enabled
SubFields.Description: Gets or sets a flag indicating whether the Push endpoint is enabled.

SubFields.Name: tag_whitelist_json
SubFields.Description: Gets or sets a JSON string containing a list of tags that are whitelisted for use by the push registration endpoint.

SubFields.Name: tags_requiring_auth
SubFields.Description:
Gets or sets a JSON string containing a list of tags that require user authentication to be used in the push registration endpoint.
Tags can consist of alphanumeric characters and the following:
'_', '@', '#', '.', ':', '-'. 
Validation should be performed at the PushRequestHandler.

SubFields.Name: dynamic_tags_json
SubFields.Description: Gets or sets a JSON string containing a list of dynamic tags that will be evaluated from user claims in the push registration endpoint.

SubFields.Name: api_definition
SubFields.Description: Information about the formal API definition for the app.

SubFields.Name: url
SubFields.Description: The URL of the API definition.

SubFields.Name: ip_address
SubFields.Description: IP address the security restriction is valid for.

SubFields.Name: subnet_mask
SubFields.Description: Subnet mask for the range of IP addresses the restriction is valid for.

ResponseFields.Name: traffic_manager_host_names
ResponseFields.Description: Azure Traffic Manager hostnames associated with the app. Read-only.

ResponseFields.Name: scm_site_also_stopped
ResponseFields.Description: true to stop SCM (KUDU) site when the app is stopped; otherwise, false. The default is false.

ResponseFields.Name: target_swap_slot
ResponseFields.Description: Specifies which deployment slot this app will swap into. Read-only.

ResponseFields.Name: hosting_environment_profile
ResponseFields.Description: App Service Environment to use for the app.

SubFields.Name: id
SubFields.Description: Resource ID of the App Service Environment.

SubFields.Name: name
SubFields.Description: Name of the App Service Environment.

SubFields.Name: type
SubFields.Description: Resource type of the App Service Environment.

ResponseFields.Name: client_affinity_enabled
ResponseFields.Description: true to enable client affinity; false to stop sending session affinity cookies, which route client requests in the same session to the same instance. Default is true.

ResponseFields.Name: client_cert_enabled
ResponseFields.Description: true to enable client certificate authentication (TLS mutual authentication); otherwise, false. Default is false.

ResponseFields.Name: host_names_disabled
ResponseFields.Description: true to disable the public hostnames of the app; otherwise, false. If true, the app is only accessible via API management process.

ResponseFields.Name: outbound_ip_addresses
ResponseFields.Description: List of IP addresses that the app uses for outbound connections (e.g. database access). Includes VIPs from tenants that site can be hosted with current settings. Read-only.

ResponseFields.Name: possible_outbound_ip_addresses
ResponseFields.Description: List of IP addresses that the app uses for outbound connections (e.g. database access). Includes VIPs from all tenants. Read-only.

ResponseFields.Name: container_size
ResponseFields.Description: Size of the function container.

ResponseFields.Name: daily_memory_time_quota
ResponseFields.Description: Maximum allowed daily memory-time quota (applicable on dynamic apps only).

ResponseFields.Name: suspended_till
ResponseFields.Description: App suspended till in case memory-time quota is exceeded.

ResponseFields.Name: max_number_of_workers
ResponseFields.Description:
Maximum number of workers.
This only applies to Functions container.

ResponseFields.Name: cloning_info
ResponseFields.Description: If specified during app creation, the app is cloned from a source app.

SubFields.Name: correlation_id
SubFields.Description:
Correlation ID of cloning operation. This ID ties multiple cloning operations
together to use the same snapshot.

SubFields.Name: clone_custom_host_names
SubFields.Description: true to clone custom hostnames from source app; otherwise, false.

SubFields.Name: clone_source_control
SubFields.Description: true to clone source control from source app; otherwise, false.

SubFields.Name: source_web_app_id
SubFields.Description:
ARM resource ID of the source app. App resource ID is of the form 
/subscriptions/{subId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Web/sites/{siteName} for production slots and 
/subscriptions/{subId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Web/sites/{siteName}/slots/{slotName} for other slots.

SubFields.Name: app_settings_overrides
SubFields.Description:
Application setting overrides for cloned app. If specified, these settings override the settings cloned 
from source app. Otherwise, application settings from source app are retained.

SubFields.Name: configure_load_balancing
SubFields.Description: true to configure load balancing for source and destination app.

SubFields.Name: traffic_manager_profile_id
SubFields.Description:
ARM resource ID of the Traffic Manager profile to use, if it exists. Traffic Manager resource ID is of the form 
/subscriptions/{subId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Network/trafficManagerProfiles/{profileName}.

SubFields.Name: traffic_manager_profile_name
SubFields.Description: Name of Traffic Manager profile to create. This is only needed if Traffic Manager profile does not already exist.

SubFields.Name: ignore_quotas
SubFields.Description: true if quotas should be ignored; otherwise, false.

ResponseFields.Name: snapshot_info
ResponseFields.Description: If specified during app creation, the app is created from a previous snapshot.

SubFields.Name: snapshot_time
SubFields.Description: Point in time in which the app recovery should be attempted, formatted as a DateTime string.

SubFields.Name: recovery_target
SubFields.Description: Specifies the web app that snapshot contents will be written to.

SubFields.Name: location
SubFields.Description: Geographical location of the target web app, e.g. SouthEastAsia, SouthCentralUS

SubFields.Name: id
SubFields.Description:
ARM resource ID of the target app. 
/subscriptions/{subId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Web/sites/{siteName} for production slots and 
/subscriptions/{subId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.Web/sites/{siteName}/slots/{slotName} for other slots.

SubFields.Name: overwrite
SubFields.Description: If true the recovery operation can overwrite source app; otherwise, false.

SubFields.Name: recover_configuration
SubFields.Description: If true, site configuration, in addition to content, will be reverted.

SubFields.Name: ignore_conflicting_host_names
SubFields.Description:
If true, custom hostname conflicts will be ignored when recovering to a target web app.
This setting is only necessary when RecoverConfiguration is enabled.

ResponseFields.Name: resource_group
ResponseFields.Description: Name of the resource group the app belongs to. Read-only.

ResponseFields.Name: is_default_container
ResponseFields.Description: true if the app is a default container; otherwise, false.

ResponseFields.Name: default_host_name
ResponseFields.Description: Default hostname of the app. Read-only.

ResponseFields.Name: slot_swap_status
ResponseFields.Description: Status of the last deployment slot swap operation.

SubFields.Name: timestamp_utc
SubFields.Description: The time the last successful slot swap completed.

SubFields.Name: source_slot_name
SubFields.Description: The source slot of the last swap operation.

SubFields.Name: destination_slot_name
SubFields.Description: The destination slot of the last swap operation.

ResponseFields.Name: https_only
ResponseFields.Description:
HttpsOnly: configures a web site to accept only https requests. Issues redirect for
http requests

SubFields.Name: principal_id
SubFields.Description: Principal Id of managed service identity.

Options.Documentation: ID of a specific scaled-out instance. This is the value of the name property in the JSON response from "GET api/sites/{siteName}/instances".

Options.Documentation: Specify "true" to include metric details in the response. It is "false" by default.

Options.Documentation: Return only metrics specified in the filter (using OData syntax). For example: $filter=(name.value eq 'Metric1' or name.value eq 'Metric2') and startTime eq '2014-01-01T00:00:00Z' and endTime eq '2014-12-31T23:59:59Z' and timeGrain eq duration'[Hour|Minute|Day]'.

Options.Name: target_slot
Options.Documentation: Destination deployment slot during swap operation.

Options.Name: preserve_vnet
Options.Documentation: true to preserve Virtual Network to the slot during swap; otherwise, false.

Options.Name: id
Options.Documentation: The ID of a specific deployment. This is the value of the name property in the JSON response from "GET /api/sites/{siteName}/deployments".

Options.Name: function_name
Options.Documentation: Function name.

Options.Name: view
Options.Documentation: The type of view. This can either be "summary" or "detailed".

Options.Name: format
Options.Documentation:
Name of the format. Valid values are: 
FileZilla3
WebDeploy -- default
Ftp. Possible values include: 'FileZilla3', 'WebDeploy', 'Ftp'

Options.Name: web_job_name
Options.Documentation: Name of Web Job.

Options.Documentation: Specify true to include deployment slots in results. The default is false, which only gives you the production slot of all apps.

ResponseFields.Name: type
ResponseFields.Description: Resource type.

ResponseFields.Name: tags
ResponseFields.Description: Resource tags.

ResponseFields.Name: app_service_plan_name
ResponseFields.Description: Name for the App Service plan.

ResponseFields.Name: worker_tier_name
ResponseFields.Description: Target worker tier assigned to the App Service plan.

ResponseFields.Name: status
ResponseFields.Description: App Service plan status. Possible values include: 'Ready', 'Pending', 'Creating'

ResponseFields.Name: subscription
ResponseFields.Description: App Service plan subscription.

ResponseFields.Name: admin_site_name
ResponseFields.Description: App Service plan administration site.

ResponseFields.Name: hosting_environment_profile
ResponseFields.Description: Specification for the App Service Environment to use for the App Service plan.

SubFields.Name: id
SubFields.Description: Resource ID of the App Service Environment.

SubFields.Name: name
SubFields.Description: Name of the App Service Environment.

SubFields.Name: type
SubFields.Description: Resource type of the App Service Environment.

ResponseFields.Name: maximum_number_of_workers
ResponseFields.Description: Maximum number of instances that can be assigned to this App Service plan.

ResponseFields.Name: geo_region
ResponseFields.Description: Geographical location for the App Service plan.

ResponseFields.Name: per_site_scaling
ResponseFields.Description: If true, apps assigned to this App Service plan can be scaled independently. If false, apps assigned to this App Service plan will scale to all instances of the plan.

ResponseFields.Name: number_of_sites
ResponseFields.Description: Number of apps assigned to this App Service plan.

ResponseFields.Name: is_spot
ResponseFields.Description: If true, this App Service Plan owns spot instances.

ResponseFields.Name: spot_expiration_time
ResponseFields.Description: The time when the server farm expires. Valid only if it is a spot server farm.

ResponseFields.Name: resource_group
ResponseFields.Description: Resource group of the App Service plan.

ResponseFields.Name: reserved
ResponseFields.Description: If Linux app service plan true, false otherwise.

ResponseFields.Name: target_worker_count
ResponseFields.Description: Scaling worker count.

ResponseFields.Name: target_worker_size_id
ResponseFields.Description: Scaling worker size ID.

ResponseFields.Name: provisioning_state
ResponseFields.Description: Provisioning state of the App Service Environment. Possible values include: 'Succeeded', 'Failed', 'Canceled', 'InProgress', 'Deleting'

SubFields.Name: tier
SubFields.Description: Service tier of the resource SKU.

SubFields.Name: size
SubFields.Description: Size specifier of the resource SKU.

SubFields.Name: family
SubFields.Description: Family code of the resource SKU.

SubFields.Name: capacity
SubFields.Description: Current number of instances assigned to the resource.

SubFields.Name: sku_capacity
SubFields.Description: Min, max, and default scale values of the SKU.

SubFields.Name: minimum
SubFields.Description: Minimum number of workers for this App Service plan SKU.

SubFields.Name: maximum
SubFields.Description: Maximum number of workers for this App Service plan SKU.

SubFields.Name: default
SubFields.Description: Default number of workers for this App Service plan SKU.

SubFields.Name: scale_type
SubFields.Description: Available scale configurations for an App Service plan.

SubFields.Name: capabilities
SubFields.Description: Capabilities of the SKU, e.g., is traffic manager enabled?

Options.Name: resource_group_name
Options.Documentation: Name of the resource group to which the resource belongs.

Options.Name: name
Options.Documentation: Name of the App Service plan.

Options.Name: skip_token
Options.Documentation: Skip to a web app in the list of webapps associated with app service plan. If specified, the resulting list will contain web apps starting from (including) the skipToken. Otherwise, the resulting list contains web apps from the start of the list

Options.Name: filter
Options.Documentation: Supported filter: $filter=state eq running. Returns only web apps that are currently running

Options.Name: top
Options.Documentation: List page size. If specified, results are paged.

Options.Name: namespace_name
Options.Documentation: The name of the Service Bus namespace.

Options.Name: relay_name
Options.Documentation: The name of the Service Bus relay.

Options.Name: details
Options.Documentation: Specify true to include instance details. The default is false.

Options.Name: vnet_name
Options.Documentation: Name of the Virtual Network.
